{{for|TP in {{XCX|-}}|Tension (XCX)}} {{spoiler}} '''Tactical Points''', commonly referred to as '''TP''', are a mechanic in {{XC3}} and {{XC3FR|sublink}}.<ref>[https://topics.nintendo.co.jp/article/a4c0a78d-e993-4fae-8c8e-62c5927040fa Xenoblade Notebook vol. 4: A thorough explanation of the Arts in ''Xenoblade 3''].</ref>
== Overview == TP is the measure of how effective the Arts performed in a [[Chain Attack (XC3)|Chain Attack]] are, and are required to continue the Chain Attack. Accumulating TP helps to increase the [[Party Gauge (XC3)|Gauge]] that activates a Chain Art once filled and determines how many characters are reactivated after the Chain Art is executed. The amount of TP generated by a selected Art is dependent on multiple factors, such as the character selected for the attack, whether the selected character shares the same Role and/or nation as the character carrying out the Chain Order, the amount of damage it inflicts or heals, and whether or not it contributes to a Combo. {{clr}}
